98
00:07:59,926 --> 00:08:03,804
...Always remember not to
forget. A child's dream is a
dream they should never get‐‐

99
00:08:03,837 --> 00:08:07,173
<i>(Zirconia)</i>
<i>Silence!...I said, silence!!</i>

100
00:08:10,711 --> 00:08:13,614
Humph!

101
00:08:13,647 --> 00:08:16,783
Cere‐Cere, the Flower Master.

102
00:08:16,817 --> 00:08:20,554
Palla‐Palla, the Ball Balancer.

103
00:08:20,621 --> 00:08:24,691
Jun‐Jun, the Acrobat.

104
00:08:24,725 --> 00:08:28,862
And Ves‐Ves, the Beast Tamer.

105
00:08:28,895 --> 00:08:30,997
We're the Amazoness Quartet!

106
00:08:31,031 --> 00:08:34,500
Yes and you're also very late!

107
00:08:34,535 --> 00:08:36,469
Where have you been
all this time?

108
00:08:36,503 --> 00:08:39,640
Frankly, you're lucky we came
at all, Granny Zirconia.

109
00:08:39,673 --> 00:08:42,809
...we may not look it, but we're
extremely busy right now.

110
00:08:42,843 --> 00:08:46,012
So if you've got something to
tell us, get on with it, okay?

111
00:08:46,046 --> 00:08:50,717
Yeah, and quick! 'Cuz
Palla‐Palla's in a hurry and
wants to go back to playing her
game.

112
00:08:50,751 --> 00:08:52,586
<i>(Zirconia)</i>
<i>Quiet, you fools!!</i>

113
00:08:52,653 --> 00:08:54,220
[gasps]

114
00:08:54,287 --> 00:08:58,592
I didn't awaken you just so you
could play and come and go at
your convenience!

115
00:08:58,659 --> 00:09:01,835
What sort of progress have you
made in your search for
Pegasus's host?

116
00:09:01,868 --> 00:09:04,370
We haven't even
started looking!

117
00:09:04,404 --> 00:09:07,574
The truth is, we don't have to
take orders from you, Granny.

118
00:09:07,608 --> 00:09:10,844
Yeah, Palla‐Palla doesn't
like being bossed around.

119
00:09:10,877 --> 00:09:13,847
You can't possibly be serious.

120
00:09:13,880 --> 00:09:15,381
And what if we are?

121
00:09:15,415 --> 00:09:17,383
Then you leave me no choice!

122
00:09:17,417 --> 00:09:20,253
If my words aren't enough
to make you obey..!

123
00:09:20,286 --> 00:09:20,921
...Then, what?

124
00:09:20,921 --> 00:09:23,056
Yeah, you gonna fight us?

125
00:09:23,089 --> 00:09:26,793
Sounds like fun. Then I can take
over this circus from you!

126
00:09:26,860 --> 00:09:29,763
Orb Attack! Hiya!

127
00:09:29,796 --> 00:09:31,264
[grunt]

128
00:09:33,767 --> 00:09:36,269
[charging up grunt]

129
00:09:49,449 --> 00:09:51,985
See ya, Granny!

130
00:09:52,553 --> 00:09:54,788
Hiya!

131
00:09:54,788 --> 00:09:58,559
[screaming]

132
00:10:00,266 --> 00:10:01,434
[grunt]

133
00:10:01,502 --> 00:10:03,403
Y' kinda blew it, didn't ya?

134
00:10:03,436 --> 00:10:06,740
Palla‐Palla got a big owwie.

135
00:10:06,773 --> 00:10:08,742
Oh, please, you're not going
to cry about it, are you?

136
00:10:08,742 --> 00:10:15,916
<i>They're strong. If all four</i>
<i>had attacked at once, I would</i>
<i>have been in real trouble...</i>

137
00:10:15,916 --> 00:10:18,284
[concentrated grunt]

138
00:10:18,351 --> 00:10:20,587
So, learned your lesson?

139
00:10:20,621 --> 00:10:23,790
<i>Dealing with you is as easy as</i>
<i>taking candy from a baby...</i>

140
00:10:23,857 --> 00:10:25,759
<i>Now, enough of this nonsense!</i>

141
00:10:25,759 --> 00:10:28,595
<i>Go and find the one in whose</i>
<i>dreams Pegasus is hiding!</i>

142
00:10:32,098 --> 00:10:33,900
Huh?

143
00:10:33,934 --> 00:10:36,302
<i>That's the girl from the arcade!</i>

144
00:10:36,369 --> 00:10:38,805
So... who's going?

145
00:10:38,872 --> 00:10:41,808
I think the one who got her
butt kicked should have to go.

146
00:10:41,875 --> 00:10:43,944
Ah, right.

147
00:10:43,944 --> 00:10:49,650
Fine, if that's the way you want
to be, okay, no problem. I'll
go.

148
00:10:52,452 --> 00:10:54,287
<i>[car horn honking]</i>

149
00:10:54,320 --> 00:10:56,456
Ah! Hi, girls!

150
00:10:56,489 --> 00:10:56,957
Huh?

151
00:10:56,957 --> 00:10:58,324
You again!

152
00:10:58,391 --> 00:11:00,466
Yeah. Sorry about all that.

153
00:11:00,500 --> 00:11:01,835
All what?

154
00:11:01,902 --> 00:11:04,304
You know, those things my
friends and I said at the
arcade...

155
00:11:04,337 --> 00:11:07,307
We didn't mean to
offend you. Really.

156
00:11:07,340 --> 00:11:08,609
What do you want?

157
00:11:08,642 --> 00:11:09,976
Just to give you these.

158
00:11:10,043 --> 00:11:13,580
Really?! You're gonna
give us two of your
tickets to the circus?

159
00:11:13,614 --> 00:11:15,749
No, you can have all of them.

160
00:11:15,782 --> 00:11:18,685
Huh? Thanks, but,
we can't accept them.

161
00:11:18,752 --> 00:11:20,353
Of course you can!

162
00:11:20,420 --> 00:11:22,789
C'mon, don't worry about it,
I've got plenty more.

163
00:11:22,823 --> 00:11:25,125
This way you can bring
all your friends.

164
00:11:25,158 --> 00:11:26,660
Hope to see you there!

165
00:11:29,763 --> 00:11:35,602
<i>(Thinking)</i>
<i>Always remember not to forget.</i>
<i>A child's dream is a dream</i>
<i>they should never get.</i>

166
00:11:36,136 --> 00:11:45,111
<i>♪ Sailor Moon</i>

167
00:11:49,182 --> 00:11:58,491
<i>♪ Sailor Moon</i>

168
00:12:04,871 --> 00:12:10,911
<i>[carnival music]</i>

169
00:12:16,917 --> 00:12:18,819
Whoahh... I've never been
to a circus before.

170
00:12:18,852 --> 00:12:23,056
Are the tents this big so that
all the elephants will fit?

171
00:12:23,056 --> 00:12:27,060
I've been to lots of circuses
and this circus seems bigger
and better in every way!

172
00:12:27,060 --> 00:12:28,729
I'm super
excited!

173
00:12:28,762 --> 00:12:29,996
Mhm!

174
00:12:30,030 --> 00:12:33,166
Calm down... You're acting like
a couple of five‐year olds!

175
00:12:33,199 --> 00:12:37,671
Let's not forget. We're only
here to help chaperone
Chibi‐Usa and Momo.

176
00:12:37,704 --> 00:12:39,205
‐Yeah, we're counting on you!
‐Yeah, we're counting on you!

177
00:12:39,239 --> 00:12:44,077
Don't you worry. We'll be right
by your side the entire time!

178
00:12:44,110 --> 00:12:46,780
Yup, so you can sit back
and enjoy the circus.

179
00:12:52,018 --> 00:12:53,620
Oh, there she is!

180
00:12:58,191 --> 00:13:02,202
Okay. Now all we have to do is
get her away from her friends.

181
00:13:02,235 --> 00:13:05,639
Leave that part to me, I'll
figure something out.

182
00:13:05,706 --> 00:13:13,213
[crowd cheering]

183
00:13:14,781 --> 00:13:24,825
<i>[circus music]</i>

184
00:13:24,825 --> 00:13:32,766
<i>[circus music]</i>

185
00:13:32,799 --> 00:13:34,601
[gasps]

186
00:13:37,137 --> 00:13:38,739
[gasps]

187
00:13:42,643 --> 00:13:46,580
[giggling]

188
00:13:49,249 --> 00:13:53,520
[crowd cheering]

189
00:14:04,838 --> 00:14:07,007
Huh??

190
00:14:24,057 --> 00:14:29,029
[awe]

191
00:14:31,331 --> 00:14:35,301
[giggling]

192
00:14:39,873 --> 00:14:44,811
[giggling]

193
00:14:52,686 --> 00:14:59,092
<i>[crowd cheering]</i>

194
00:14:59,159 --> 00:15:01,735
Huh? What's wrong?

195
00:15:04,370 --> 00:15:07,240
Hey‐‐ Momo! Where're you going?
|

196
00:15:07,240 --> 00:15:09,209
The show, it's not over!

197
00:15:12,378 --> 00:15:14,247
Momo...

198
00:15:15,081 --> 00:15:18,084
Usagi! Something's wrong!

199
00:15:29,896 --> 00:15:35,135
[giggling]

200
00:15:51,384 --> 00:15:56,623
Wait‐‐... What just
happened? How did I‐‐?

201
00:15:57,323 --> 00:16:00,160
[giggling]

202
00:16:00,226 --> 00:16:02,135
Thank you so much for coming.

203
00:16:02,969 --> 00:16:06,072
Look, there she is! Momo‐‐!

204
00:16:06,106 --> 00:16:08,975
Hold on! I think we should
Transform first...

205
00:16:09,009 --> 00:16:10,310
Good Idea...

206
00:16:18,284 --> 00:16:22,422
[giggling]

207
00:16:22,455 --> 00:16:26,326
Who‐‐ Who are you?

208
00:16:26,827 --> 00:16:30,764
Now, let's have a look at that
Dream Mirror of yours, shall we?

209
00:16:33,834 --> 00:16:35,836
Orb Shot!

210
00:16:38,038 --> 00:16:39,973
Ahh!

211
00:16:53,219 --> 00:16:56,857
Huh?...That sure isn't
a Golden Mirror.

212
00:16:57,023 --> 00:16:58,692
So disappointing.

213
00:16:58,725 --> 00:17:02,202
Granny Zirconia. The old witch
gave us a bum lead!

214
00:17:02,235 --> 00:17:03,403
<i>(Sailor Moon)</i>
<i>Hold it right there!</i>

215
00:17:03,837 --> 00:17:05,972
This was meant to be a
fun night at the circus!

216
00:17:06,006 --> 00:17:08,141
And you're going to
pay for ruining it!

217
00:17:08,174 --> 00:17:09,976
We're the Sailor Guardians...

218
00:17:10,010 --> 00:17:11,377
...who fight for
love and justice!

219
00:17:11,377 --> 00:17:13,213
In the name of the Moon...

220
00:17:13,213 --> 00:17:14,981
we'll punish you!

221
00:17:15,015 --> 00:17:20,186
Aha. So you're those Sailor
Guardians Granny told us about.

222
00:17:20,320 --> 00:17:22,422
I'm delighted to make
your acquaintance

223
00:17:22,488 --> 00:17:25,892
Seriously? Palla‐Palla's not
delighted at all!

224
00:17:25,892 --> 00:17:28,161
It's called sarcasm, dear.

225
00:17:28,194 --> 00:17:31,197
It was nice of you to drop
in, but don't interfere.

226
00:17:31,231 --> 00:17:34,935
My wild beasts are hungry
and it's feeding time.

227
00:17:35,001 --> 00:17:37,103
What kind of wild beasts?

228
00:17:37,170 --> 00:17:41,508
Come forth, my Lemures!
Gara‐Gara Girl, the
Dream‐Eating Serpent!

229
00:17:41,542 --> 00:17:46,046
Gara‐Gara Gara‐Gara Gara‐Gara!

230
00:17:48,081 --> 00:17:50,884
Gara‐Gara Girl!

231
00:17:50,917 --> 00:17:52,085
[hissing]

232
00:17:52,118 --> 00:17:54,054
Think she's hungry for
a dream mirror?

233
00:17:54,087 --> 00:17:57,524
Gara‐Gara Girl, eat it while
it's nice and ripe!

234
00:17:57,558 --> 00:18:00,460
[attack roar]

235
00:18:00,527 --> 00:18:02,803
She took Momo's Dream Mirror!

236
00:18:02,869 --> 00:18:05,271
[gulp]

237
00:18:06,272 --> 00:18:10,410
Thanks for the meal, it was
delicious!

238
00:18:11,978 --> 00:18:13,814
How could you!?

239
00:18:13,880 --> 00:18:15,115
Chibi Moon!

240
00:18:16,082 --> 00:18:19,119
[attack roar]

241
00:18:21,054 --> 00:18:23,957
[attack grunts]

242
00:18:23,957 --> 00:18:28,161
What should we do? If we attack
now, we risk hurting Chibi Moon!

243
00:18:28,228 --> 00:18:31,798
Huh. What are they so
upset about? It's only
a Dream Mirror.

244
00:18:31,832 --> 00:18:34,167
And a useless one at that.

245
00:18:34,234 --> 00:18:36,402
The girl should be thanking
us for disposing of it.

246
00:18:36,436 --> 00:18:40,106
Momo's dreams aren't
useless! Give 'em back!

247
00:18:40,140 --> 00:18:42,142
[grunt]

248
00:18:42,976 --> 00:18:44,344
Ahh!

249
00:18:44,410 --> 00:18:45,411
No!

250
00:18:45,445 --> 00:18:47,147
You'll pay for that!...

251
00:18:47,447 --> 00:18:49,816
Fire Soul!

252
00:18:50,350 --> 00:18:56,256
Ow! Hot! Hot! I'm a living
being, so I can't stand heat!

253
00:18:56,356 --> 00:18:57,824
Now's our chance.

254
00:18:59,459 --> 00:19:05,271
Please, Pegasus! Protect
everyone's dream!

255
00:19:05,305 --> 00:19:10,043
Twinkle Yell!

256
00:19:14,380 --> 00:19:16,850
[neigh]

257
00:19:17,017 --> 00:19:18,018
Check it out!

258
00:19:18,051 --> 00:19:19,352
That's Pegasus?

259
00:19:19,385 --> 00:19:22,222
[neigh]

260
00:19:33,199 --> 00:19:41,241
Moon Gorgeous Meditation!

261
00:19:53,386 --> 00:19:57,423
Stage Out!

262
00:20:02,168 --> 00:20:04,170
Party's over...

263
00:20:08,875 --> 00:20:13,479
<i>They're gone!</i>

264
00:20:13,514 --> 00:20:14,781
[gasp]

265
00:20:14,815 --> 00:20:18,151
Hey. We better return
Momo's Dream Mirror to
her, don'tcha think?

266
00:20:18,184 --> 00:20:19,853
Mhm!

267
00:20:19,986 --> 00:20:23,323
<i>(Masseurs)</i>
<i>Rub down, rub down, Push and</i>
<i>press, Prod and poke, Lose that</i>
<i>stress.</i>

268
00:20:23,356 --> 00:20:32,533
Rub down, rub down, Push and
press, Prod and poke, Lose that
stress....

269
00:20:32,566 --> 00:20:34,167
Ah, this is heaven!

270
00:20:34,200 --> 00:20:36,369
Yeah, right there,
that's the spot.

271
00:20:36,369 --> 00:20:42,142
[groan] Looks like we may be
stuck with this lame
Pegasus‐finding job for awhile.

272
00:20:42,175 --> 00:20:44,477
Hope not... It's too much work.

273
00:20:44,511 --> 00:20:47,514
Palla‐Palla likes to play
a lot more than work.

274
00:20:47,548 --> 00:20:54,521
Well, if nobody else wants to
do it... then I guess I'll just
have to step up and volunteer to
go after the next target.

275
00:20:54,555 --> 00:20:57,558
No, no. I feel bad making
you do all the work, Ves‐Ves.

276
00:20:57,591 --> 00:20:59,560
I'll do the next one.

277
00:20:59,560 --> 00:21:02,335
That's all right, you girls
relax. I'll do it.

278
00:21:02,368 --> 00:21:05,939
Oh yeah, Funny how all of a
sudden everyone wants to do it.

279
00:21:06,006 --> 00:21:11,411
[dreamy sigh] Did anybody else
think that Pegasus was really,
really pretty?

280
00:21:11,411 --> 00:21:12,679
Totally.

281
00:21:12,713 --> 00:21:15,448
And we're supposed to just hand
him over to Granny Zirconia...

282
00:21:15,516 --> 00:21:17,518
Seems like such a waste.

283
00:21:19,285 --> 00:21:24,257
I suspect that sooner or later
those girls will come to the
conclusion that they should keep

284
00:21:24,257 --> 00:21:26,426
Pegasus and his power
for themselves.

285
00:21:26,426 --> 00:21:30,096
I don't trust them.

286
00:21:30,096 --> 00:21:35,536
I fear that if we don't do
something, they will eventually
become a threat.

287
00:21:35,569 --> 00:21:37,571
Leave them be.

288
00:21:37,604 --> 00:21:40,373
Let them go about their
business as they see fit.

289
00:21:40,406 --> 00:21:43,610
Your job is to keep an
eye on them, that's all.

290
00:21:43,644 --> 00:21:46,379
But, my queen, I‐‐

291
00:21:47,113 --> 00:21:48,615
Are you questioning my orders?

292
00:21:48,615 --> 00:21:51,618
Me? No. Never, your majesty.

293
00:21:51,618 --> 00:21:54,154
I will do just as
you say, of course.

294
00:21:54,220 --> 00:22:00,594
That's right. You will do
whatever I tell you to do and
you will do it without
hesitation...

295
00:22:00,627 --> 00:22:07,240
...after all, I am the
forever‐beautiful Nehalennia,
the True Queen of the Moon.

296
00:22:07,273 --> 00:22:13,479
[evil chuckle]

297
00:22:18,418 --> 00:22:28,161
♪

298
00:22:28,161 --> 00:22:48,181
♪

299
00:22:48,181 --> 00:23:08,208
♪

300
00:23:08,208 --> 00:23:28,228
♪

301
00:23:28,228 --> 00:23:48,248
♪

302
00:23:52,252 --> 00:23:55,622
(<i>Ami</i>
<i>I heard the most</i>
<i>wonderful melody...</i>

303
00:23:55,689 --> 00:23:58,559
<i>I feel like something inside</i>
<i>of me is about to change...!</i>

304
00:23:58,592 --> 00:24:00,060
<i>(Usagi)</i>
<i>What do you mean, Ami?</i>

305
00:24:00,093 --> 00:24:03,403
<i>(Ami)</i>
<i>I can't describe it, it's like</i>
<i>something tickling my heart</i>

306
00:24:03,436 --> 00:24:04,204
<i>or is it tingling...?</i>

307
00:24:04,237 --> 00:24:05,606
<i>(Usagi)</i>
<i>Wait, could it be..??</i>

308
00:24:05,639 --> 00:24:06,573
<i>(Ami)</i>
<i>What?</i>

309
00:24:06,607 --> 00:24:08,441
<i>(Usagi)</i>
<i>Ami! Are you falling in love?!</i>

310
00:24:08,474 --> 00:24:10,410
<i>(Ami)</i>
<i>No! That's not it!</i>

311
00:24:10,476 --> 00:24:15,749
<i>(Usagi)</i>
<i>Next time on Sailor Moon SuperS:</i>
<i>"True Power Explodes: Ami's</i>
<i>Melody of the Heart."</i>

312
00:24:15,782 --> 00:24:17,884
<i>(Usagi)</i>
<i>The moonlight is a</i>
<i>messenger of love.</i>

